decks.notes: The deck is focused on utilizing graveyard recursion and self-mill to quickly fill the graveyard with key combo pieces like Stinkweed Imp, Narcomoeba, and Prized Amalgam. Combo pieces like Creeping Chill and Ichorid help to deal damage and bring back creatures from the graveyard. The deck also includes disruption cards like Force of Will, Grief, and Force of Negation to protect the combo and disrupt the opponent. Bazaar of Baghdad is used to quickly put cards into the graveyard. The goal of the deck is to overwhelm the opponent with a quick and powerful combo.

The deck focuses on using hatebears to disrupt opponents while applying pressure with aggressive creatures. It utilizes cards like Anointed Peacekeeper, Archon of Emeria, and Chancellor of the Annex to slow down the opponent's game plan, while also utilizing cards like Stillmoon Cavalier and Seasoned Dungeoneer to apply pressure and close out the game quickly. The deck also includes powerful mana acceleration with cards like Ancient Tomb and Moxen to get ahead early and maintain control of the game. The key strategy is to disrupt the opponent's plans while applying pressure to secure a victory.

The deck focuses on controlling the game through counterspells, removal, and disruptive creatures like Lavinia, Azorius Renegade. It utilizes powerful cards like Force of Will, Swords to Plowshares, and Wasteland to disrupt opponents while drawing cards with Ancestral Recall and digging through the deck with Brainstorm, Dig Through Time, and Treasure Cruise. The inclusion of a companion, Lurrus of the Dream-Den, allows for additional value by recurring low-cost permanents. Overall, the deck aims to outvalue opponents through efficient answers and card advantage.
